# Audric Design System (Geist DS)

**Two layers.** The Geist *primitives* (`--ds-*` ramps, `--fg`, `--bg`) come from **`@t2000/ui`** — the cross-brand single source of truth (`globals.css` does `@import "@t2000/ui/tokens" layer(base)`). Audric's *brand-semantic mapping* (the shadcn tokens + the cyan `--signal`) lives in `apps/web-v2/app/globals.css`. Edit Audric's look here in `globals.css`; never edit `@t2000/ui` primitives (that moves every t2000 brand). See `t2000/.cursor/rules/geist-ds.mdc` for the package-level contract.

Prototype reference: `t2000-AFI/audric/phase2-*.html` (founder-local, gitignored — the canonical phase2 spec the R6.x Geist migration was rebuilt against).

> **R6.9 (2026-05-30) — the legacy Agentic Design System (ADS) was decommissioned.** The raw colour ramps (`--n/--r/--g/--y/--o/--b` families), the `surface-*` / `fg-*` / `border-default|subtle|focus` semantic aliases, the `*-fg|bg|border|solid` status family, and the `.ads-*` typography ramp classes are **GONE**. Every surface now reads the Geist-rooted shadcn tokens. `pnpm check:ads` (`scripts/check-ads-tokens.mts`) fails CI on any reintroduction. **Do not write ADS tokens** — they will not resolve and will break the build gate.

## Rule 1 — Semantic tokens only, no raw colors

Every color value resolves through a Geist-rooted shadcn token. Never use raw hex, never use Tailwind default colors (`red-400`, `gray-500`, `bg-white`), never use the removed ADS aliases.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — raw hex / Tailwind defaults
<div className="bg-white border border-gray-200 text-red-500">
<div className="bg-[#F7F7F7] text-[#191919]">

// ❌ BAD — removed ADS tokens (check:ads fails CI)
<div className="bg-surface-card text-fg-primary border-border-subtle text-error-fg">

// ✅ GOOD — Geist-rooted shadcn tokens
<div className="bg-card text-foreground border border-border">
<div className="bg-muted text-muted-foreground">
```

Available semantic groups (full list in `globals.css`):

- **Surface / fg**: `bg-background` / `text-foreground`, `bg-card` / `text-card-foreground`, `bg-popover`, `bg-muted` / `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-secondary`, `bg-accent`
- **Brand**: `bg-primary` / `text-primary-foreground` (primary = `--fg`, i.e. near-black/near-white per theme)
- **Border / ring / input**: `border-border`, `ring-ring`, `bg-input`; the stronger hairline is `border-[var(--border-strong)]` (a Geist token)
- **Status** (bare utilities only — the `-fg/-bg/-border/-solid` suffixes are the banned ADS variants): `text-success` / `bg-success`, `text-warning` / `bg-warning`, `text-info`, `text-destructive` / `bg-destructive`
- **Signal** — Audric's single accent (cyan, signal-only): `text-signal` / `bg-signal` / `bg-signal-bg`. Use for the live dot, the AudricMark thinking state, settled-tx checks. **Never** on CTAs / links / focus rings.
- **Sidebar**: `bg-sidebar`, `text-sidebar-foreground`, `bg-sidebar-accent`, `border-sidebar-border`, etc.
- **Charts**: `--chart-1` … `--chart-5` (Geist gray ramp steps)
- **Geist ramps** (when a shadcn token doesn't exist): `var(--ds-gray-*)`, `var(--ds-blue-700)`, `var(--ds-teal-700)`, `var(--ds-amber-700)`, etc.

## Rule 2 — Typography uses Geist + `font-{sans,serif,mono}`

Geist DS is **Geist + Geist Mono only** (New York + Departure Mono were ADS v1 leftovers, stripped from the app UI in R6.4).

- `font-sans` — Geist Sans. Default body. Set on `<body>`.
- `font-serif` — also resolves to Geist (DS display = Geist). Headlines, balances, hero numerals.
- `font-mono` — Geist Mono. Labels, eyebrows, badges, mono numerals. Usually uppercase + tracking.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — Tailwind size/weight ad-hoc, or removed .ads-* ramp class
<h1 className="text-3xl font-bold">Balance</h1>
<h1 className="ads-h1">Balance</h1>

// ✅ GOOD — Geist stacks + explicit scale; mono labels uppercase + tracked
<h1 className="font-serif text-2xl">Balance</h1>
<span className="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-muted-foreground">Available</span>
```

Numerals: use `tabular-nums` for aligned columns.

## Rule 3 — Let tokens flip; theming is automatic

Theme is driven by `next-themes` with a **dual attribute** (`attribute={["class", "data-theme"]}` in `app/layout.tsx`):

- `data-theme` drives the **Geist DS ramp** — Geist flips grayscale + blue + backgrounds per theme automatically, so the shadcn tokens that alias `--ds-*` (or `color-mix` off `--fg`) flip **with no `.dark` override needed**.
- The `.dark` class drives Audric's `dark:` Tailwind variant (`@custom-variant dark (&:is(.dark, .dark *))` in `globals.css`) + the per-theme shadow / signal overrides.

**Prefer letting tokens flip automatically.** Reach for a `dark:` variant only when a value genuinely can't be expressed through a theme-flipping token (e.g. a one-off shadow). If something looks wrong in dark, fix it at the token layer first.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — hand-branching on theme, or hardcoding both sides
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-black text-black dark:text-white">
const bg = theme === 'dark' ? 'bg-zinc-900' : 'bg-white';

// ✅ GOOD — tokens flip automatically via data-theme (Geist) + .dark (shadows)
<div className="bg-card text-foreground">
```

Light is the canonical first impression (default theme is `light`). The theme switcher lives in Settings → Appearance (Light / Dark / System).

## Rule 4 — New screens reference the phase2 prototype

Before building a new component or panel, check the corresponding `t2000-AFI/audric/phase2-*.html` spec for the canonical layout, spacing, and tokens. Cite the prototype path in a header comment so the next reader can diff against it:

```tsx
// [R6.x] Rebuilt to `t2000-AFI/audric/phase2-wallet-card.html`.
export function BalanceCardV2() { ... }
```

## Quick checklist before opening a PR with new UI

- [ ] No raw hex / Tailwind default colors in `className` or inline styles
- [ ] No removed ADS tokens (`surface-*`, `fg-*`, `border-default|subtle|focus`, `*-fg|bg|border|solid`, `.ads-*`) — run `pnpm check:ads`
- [ ] Colors use Geist-rooted shadcn tokens (`bg-card`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `text-success`, `text-signal`, …)
- [ ] Typography uses `font-{sans,serif,mono}` (all Geist) + explicit scale; mono labels uppercase + tracked
- [ ] Renders correctly in both themes — let tokens flip; `dark:` only as a last resort
- [ ] Header comment cites the `phase2-*.html` prototype path
